---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import InstallCommand from '@/components/InstallCommand.astro';

const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<DocsLayout title="Getting Started">
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>

  <p class="lead text-lg text-[var(--muted)] mb-8">
    MSP Claude Plugins supercharge Claude Code for Managed Service Provider workflows.
    Get up and running in under 60 seconds.
  </p>

  <h2>What are MSP Claude Plugins?</h2>

  <p>
    MSP Claude Plugins is a collection of Claude Code plugins designed specifically for
    Managed Service Providers. Each plugin provides:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Skills</strong> - Domain knowledge that teaches Claude about MSP platforms, terminology, and best practices</li>
    <li><strong>Commands</strong> - Slash commands that provide structured prompts for common tasks</li>
    <li><strong>API Patterns</strong> - Knowledge of authentication, rate limiting, and error handling for each platform</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Quick Install</h2>

  <p>
    The fastest path is the hosted WYRE MCP Gateway. In Claude Code, one command wires up every
    supported vendor:
  </p>

  <pre><code class="language-bash">claude mcp add --scope user --transport http msp-mcp-gateway https://mcp.wyre.ai/v1/mcp</code></pre>

  <p>
    On Claude Desktop or Claude.ai, use the Connectors UI with URL
    <code>https://mcp.wyre.ai/v1/mcp</code> — see the
    <a href={`${baseUrl}getting-started/gateway/`}>Gateway setup guide</a> for step-by-step
    instructions on each surface.
  </p>

  <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)] mt-2">
    Prefer to skip the gateway and install plugins (skills and commands) directly?
    Run the marketplace command:
  </p>

  <div class="not-prose my-4">
    <InstallCommand />
  </div>

  <h2>What&apos;s Included</h2>

  <p>
    The plugin collection covers 30+ MSP platforms across PSA, RMM, documentation,
    security, productivity, and accounting. Selected examples:
  </p>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 not-prose my-6">
    <div class="card">
      <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">PSA &amp; RMM</h3>
      <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)] space-y-1">
        <li>Autotask PSA, Datto RMM</li>
        <li>ConnectWise PSA &amp; Automate</li>
        <li>HaloPSA, Syncro, Atera</li>
        <li>SuperOps.ai, NinjaOne</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Documentation &amp; Security</h3>
      <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)] space-y-1">
        <li>IT Glue, Hudu, Liongard</li>
        <li>SentinelOne, Huntress</li>
        <li>Blumira, RocketCyber</li>
        <li>KnowBe4, SpamTitan</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Productivity &amp; Billing</h3>
      <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)] space-y-1">
        <li>Microsoft 365</li>
        <li>Pax8, Sherweb</li>
        <li>QuickBooks, Xero</li>
        <li>PandaDoc, Salesbuildr</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)] mt-2">
    See the full list on the <a href={`${baseUrl}plugins/`}>Plugins page</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Next Steps</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><a href={`${baseUrl}getting-started/installation/`}>Installation Guide</a> - Detailed installation options</li>
    <li><a href={`${baseUrl}getting-started/quick-start/`}>Quick Start</a> - Your first workflow with plugins</li>
    <li><a href={`${baseUrl}getting-started/deployment/`}>Deployment</a> - Deploy MCP servers with Docker, DigitalOcean, or Cloudflare</li>
    <li><a href={`${baseUrl}plugins/`}>Browse Plugins</a> - Explore all available plugins</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
